cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "el: an LLM-free, action-grounded PC agent with dual-memory architecture"
abstract: >
  el is an experimental PC agent that does not use an LLM. Instead, it pairs a
  symbolic skill registry (exact episodic memory, grows by local plasticity on
  verified action outcomes) with a small Decision-Transformer-style Action
  Transformer (statistical generalization, trained on (command, state, action,
  outcome) tokenized sequences). The architecture is inspired by McClelland's
  Complementary Learning Systems (1995). Training signal is verified action
  outcomes rather than next-token prediction. Claim is NOT that el outperforms
  frontier LLMs on language tasks, but that it occupies an unexplored combination:
  no LLM + real OS substrate + dual symbolic-neural memory + action tokenization.
